HEADWORD: Achromic
<hw>A*chro"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ colorless;
<?/ priv. + <?/ color.]</ety> <def>Free from color; colorless; <as>as,
in <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld>, the <ex>achromic</ex> point of a starch
solution acted upon by an amylolytic enzyme is the point at which it
fails to give any color with iodine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

